This paper deals with the issue of bias in artificial intelligence models, which is a topic that falls under the category of Computational Social Science (cs.CY). The paper specifically focuses on the use of viewer ratings of TEDTalks, which involves the use of machine learning algorithms (cs.AI) to analyze the data. The paper also discusses strategies for detecting and mitigating bias, which involves the use of statistical methods (cs.SI) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper's emphasis on fairness and removing unfairness in AI suggests that it may also fall under the category of Machine Learning (cs.LG).
